parameters:
A pleasantly warm breeze, carrying the salty scent of
the sea, gently blows towards me.
Ah, is this heaven? I might ascend like this...

Are you going to play beach ball right away? But you're
sitting alone under the parasol like a lonely
introvert, biting into solitude.
No, I was just... watching everyone.

No, wait a minute. Renka-chan, your word choice is
strange.

As I thought, that's how it is. Senpai isn't a monkey
after all.

I wonder what they're thinking behind that smiling
face.

In the midst of that, I could hear the sound of someone
stepping on the sand from behind.
What's going on? What are you two doing together?

Hikaru instead of being alone in a place like this,
why don't we play with a beach ball?
When I turned around, there were Kanae and Tsugumi.
Ah, Renka-chan! Your swimsuit is cute!
Kanae-senpai is also very dear to me.

While the two of them were giggling and making a fuss while
holding hands, Tsugumi approached me and placed her
hand on top of my head.
Because I was in the sea.
Because I was in the sea.

I swiftly dodge the arm swinging fiercely and quickly
enter the sea.
Then, with a 'thud' sound, stars appeared in my mind.
And then, a white cloth floated up like a ghost.
Geez! What are you doing, Hikaru!
Casper's true identity was not a ghost, but Akane!
Ah, it was Akane. I thought it was Misaki.

I didn't think you should go diving if you think
there's a water spirit!

I'll buy you a pork cutlet bowl later, so please forgive
me.
So, why were you floating like a jellyfish?

It feels nice to float aimlessly on the water's surface
on such a sunny day!
Eh~ Isn't that the case for you, Hikaru?

I'm afraid of being carried away somewhere while doing
that.
Well, I'm not really that good at swimming.
Poor Hikaru, who doesn't know the joy of this.
(If you say "Is that so?" then it's not good)

Boss, isn't there something a little off about the
pronunciation?
Huh? The one with the strange ears is you, right?
Huh? There are six lottery tickets?

Since Taiyo and I participating together would be unfair...
We've decided not to join.

No, isn't it? This should be a game that's enjoyable
just by watching.
Ah, I'm in the same group as Hikaru!
Oh, that's right. Nice to meet you, Kanae.
